%I A393605 #23 Mar 08 2026 23:59:12
%S A393605 0,0,1,3,1,2,4,6,8,6,2,10,8,16,16
%N A393605 a(n) is the number of optimal 2-Golomb rulers of length n.
%C A393605 A 2-Golomb ruler refers to a set of integers for which no nonzero d has more than 2 representations as a difference of elements of the set. An optimal Golomb ruler is a set constructed with the minimum possible diameter. The optimal lengths of said rulers were sourced from A392461.
%C A393605 It appears that a(2*n) = A023360(n + 3) for n>=2
%H A393605 Aditya Gupta, <a href="https://github.com/Dirac3011/GolombRuler2/blob/main/printer.cpp">Code for generating 2-Golomb rulers</a>
%e A393605 For n = 8, the a(8) = 6 solutions are
%e A393605     [0, 1, 2, 6, 10, 13, 16, 18],
%e A393605     [0, 1, 3, 7,  9, 14, 17, 18],
%e A393605     [0, 1, 3, 8, 12, 14, 17, 18],
%e A393605     [0, 1, 4, 6, 10, 15, 17, 18],
%e A393605     [0, 1, 4, 9, 11, 15, 17, 18],
%e A393605     [0, 2, 5, 8, 12, 16, 17, 18].
%Y A393605 Cf. A023360, A392461.
%K A393605 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A393605 1,4
%A A393605 _Aditya A Gupta_, Feb 23 2026
